  "prompt": "What type of grapes are used to make wine?",
  "response": "Various types of grapes are used to make wine, and they can be broadly categorized into two main groups: red grapes and white grapes.\n\n1. **Red Grapes**: These grapes are used to produce red and ros\u00e9 wines. Some popular red grape varieties include:\n   - Cabernet Sauvignon\n   - Merlot\n   - Pinot Noir\n   - Syrah/Shiraz\n   - Zinfandel\n   - Malbec\n   - Tempranillo\n\n2. **White Grapes**: These grapes are typically used for white wines. Some common white grape varieties include:\n   - Chardonnay\n   - Sauvignon Blanc\n   - Riesling\n   - Pinot Grigio/Pinot Gris\n   - Chenin Blanc\n   - Gew\u00fcrztraminer\n   - Viognier\n\nIn addition to these, there are many other lesser-known grape varieties used in winemaking around the world. Some regions may also be known for unique indigenous grape varieties. Each grape variety contributes distinct flavors, aromas, and characteristics to the wine.",
